ACT Π. SCENE 4.

Philto asks Lesbonicus to give his sister to Lysiteles in marriage without dowry. Lesbonicus assents after some hesitation to the mar· riage3 but declares his intention of giving all that remains of his property as a dowry. The Act concludes without this point being settled. The audacious fictions by which Stasimus persuades Philto to reject the land offered by Lesbonicus, form one of the most amusing features in the play, second only to the dialogue between Charmides and the Sycophant.
